
Cotton:
    7,000–29,000 L of water per kg of cotton fiber depending on irrigation and climate.  https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228377230_The_Water_Footprint_of_Cotton_Consumption

    10,000–17,000 L of water per kg of cotton lint (global estimate).  https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2772912525000752
    
    Cotton cultivation accounts for ~2.6% of global water use. https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228377230_The_Water_Footprint_of_Cotton_Consumption

    1.15–6.07 kg CO₂ per kg of cotton fiber depending on farming practices and energy use. https://www.carbonfact.com/blog/knowledge/carbon-footprint-cotton

    Cotton production accounts for 8.3% of the global blue water footprint of crop production. https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2666791624000204

Polyester:
    >30 kg CO₂ per kg of polyester fabric across its full lifecycle. https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7787125/ 

    Producing the PET polymer used in one polyester T-shirt requires ~7.6 kWh of energy and emits ~5.95 kg CO₂. https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-29/polyester-t-shirt-lifecycle-carbon-emissions-environment/102726502

    Polyester accounts for ~59% of global fiber production and ~43% of raw-material emissions in textiles. https://www.vogue.com/article/material-production-reaches-record-heights-and-emissions-grow

    Polyester textile production emits 25,700 kg CO₂ per tonne of textile produced (~25.7 kg per kg). https://www.climatiq.io/data/emission-factor/da27154d-b0ca-43b9-8918-db1f7597d57

    In 2022, 70 million barrels of oil were required to produce polyester. It’s not biodegradable, and it emits microplastics. https://unric.org/en/from-petroleum-to-pollution-the-cost-of-polyester/

    Washing one polyester shirt every two weeks can release approximately 52,000 microplastic fibres annually https://unric.org/en/from-petroleum-to-pollution-the-cost-of-polyester/

    synthetic textiles are responsible for 35% of the microplastics in our oceans today https://unric.org/en/from-petroleum-to-pollution-the-cost-of-polyester/

