    textile production is estimated to be responsible for about 20% of global clean water pollution as a result of dyeing and finishing products. https://unric.org/en/from-petroleum-to-pollution-the-cost-of-polyester/

    the fashion industry is responsible for 10% of the world’s carbon emissions. https://unric.org/en/from-petroleum-to-pollution-the-cost-of-polyester/